&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse - Medical Receiving Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Band 5 Staff Nurses to work within the Medical Receiving Unit (MRU). MRU is a busy and friendly unit with a high turnover of patients both ambulatory and acutely unwell.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting an enthusiastic and highly motivated nurse who is ready for a new challenge in their career. We require staff to provide high quality care to all our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we provide a supportive environment, full induction and preceptorship with many opportunities to develop your skills and knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Entry Requirements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants must be currently registered with the NMC.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alternatively, this post is suitable for newly qualified individuals, if you are currently pending your registration then please tick “YES” to have a professional registration and state in your supporting information that you are pending your pin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
